The tool `setup.tools.createNewWorkspace` has an invalid name and causes API errors when it's given in any Sonnet request.

> {"code":"failed","message":"Sorry, your request failed. Please try again. Request id: 79a55962-afc5-4c2c-8c3a-8ebdc693713d\n\nReason: Request Failed: 400 {\"error\":{\"message\":\"tools.13.custom.name: String should match pattern '^[a-zA-Z0-9_-]{1,128}$'\",\"code\":\"invalid_request_body\"}}\n","confirmationButtons":[{"data":{"copilotContinueOnError":true},"label":"Try Again"}],"responseIsIncomplete":true}

We should at least rename it, though you may also consider removing it since I think the usage is probably pretty low if this hasn't been raised before ^
